    "List of AUX devices that should NOT be displayed. This field requires a regular expression and cannot be left empty. If you do not want to filter any devices, you must provide a regex that matches none of the entries.\n\nExamples:\n\nNo entries: /^none$/\nFilter out 'Ground Floor': /^Ground Floor$/\nFilter out 'Ground Floor' and 'First Floor': /^Ground Floor$|^First Floor$/\nFilter out everything starting with 'Distributor': /^Distributor.*$/": "Lista de dispositivos AUX que NO deben mostrarse. Este campo requiere una expresión regular y no puede quedar vacío. Si no quieres filtrar ningún dispositivo, debes proporcionar una regex que no coincida con ninguna de las entradas.\n\nEjemplos:\n\nSin entradas: /^none$/\nFiltrar 'Ground Floor': /^Ground Floor$/\nFiltrar 'Ground Floor' y 'First Floor': /^Ground Floor$|^First Floor$/\nFiltrar todo lo que empiece por 'Distributor': /^Distributor.*$/",
    "List of EXT devices that should NOT be displayed. This field requires a regular expression and cannot be left empty. If you do not want to filter any devices, you must provide a regex that matches none of the entries.\n\nExamples:\n\nNo entries: /^none$/\nFilter out 'Ground Floor': /^Ground Floor$/\nFilter out 'Ground Floor' and 'First Floor': /^Ground Floor$|^First Floor$/\nFilter out everything starting with 'Distributor': /^Distributor.*$/": "Lista de dispositivos EXT que NO deben mostrarse. Este campo requiere una expresión regular y no puede quedar vacío. Si no quieres filtrar ningún dispositivo, debes proporcionar una regex que no coincida con ninguna de las entradas.\n\nEjemplos:\n\nSin entradas: /^none$/\nFiltrar 'Ground Floor': /^Ground Floor$/\nFiltrar 'Ground Floor' y 'First Floor': /^Ground Floor$|^First Floor$/\nFiltrar todo lo que empiece por 'Distributor': /^Distributor.*$/",
    "List of loadpoints that should NOT be displayed. The expression is a regular expression that must start and end with /. It must not be empty; if nothing should be filtered, provide a regular expression that matches none of the entries.\n\nExamples:\nNo entries: /^none$/\nFilter out 'Garage': /^Garage$/\nFilter out 'Garage' and 'Parking Spot': /^Garage$|^Parking Spot$/\nFilter out everything that starts with 'foo': /^foo.*$/": "List of loadpoints that should NOT be displayed. The expression is a regular expression that must start and end with /. It must not be empty; if nothing should be filtered, provide a regular expression that matches none of the entries.\n\nExamples:\nNo entries: /^none$/\nFilter out 'Garage': /^Garage$/\nFilter out 'Garage' and 'Parking Spot': /^Garage$|^Parking Spot$/\nFilter out everything that starts with 'foo': /^foo.*$/",
    "List of loadpoints that should NOT be displayed. This field requires a regular expression and cannot be left empty. If you do not want to filter any entries, you must provide a regex that does not match any existing loadpoint.\n\nExamples:\n\nNo entries: ^none$\nFilter out 'Garage': ^Garage$\nFilter out 'Garage' and 'Parking Spot': ^Garage$|^Parking Spot$\nFilter out everything starting with 'foo': ^foo.*$": "Lista de puntos de carga que NO deben mostrarse. Este campo requiere una expresión regular y no puede quedar vacío. Si no quieres filtrar ninguna entrada, debes proporcionar una regex que no coincida con ningún punto de carga existente.\n\nEjemplos:\n\nSin entradas: ^none$\nFiltrar 'Garage': ^Garage$\nFiltrar 'Garage' y 'Parking Spot': ^Garage$|^Parking Spot$\nFiltrar todo lo que empiece por 'foo': ^foo.*$",
    "List of vehicles that should NOT be displayed. This field must contain a regular expression and cannot be left empty. If you do not want to filter any vehicles, you must provide a regex that matches none of the entries.\n\nExamples:\n\nNo entries: ^none$\nFilter out 'Garage': ^Garage$\nFilter out 'Garage' and 'Parking Spot': ^Garage$|^Parking Spot$\nFilter out vehicles ending with '(offline)': ^.*\\(offline\\)$": "Lista de vehículos que NO deben mostrarse. Este campo debe contener una expresión regular y no puede quedar vacío. Si no quieres filtrar ningún vehículo, debes proporcionar una regex que no coincida con ninguna de las entradas.\n\nEjemplos:\n\nSin entradas: ^none$\nFiltrar 'Garage': ^Garage$\nFiltrar 'Garage' y 'Parking Spot': ^Garage$|^Parking Spot$\nFiltrar vehículos que terminen en '(offline)': ^.*\\(offline\\)$",
